WEBVTT

00:06.589 --> 00:08.508
McQUEEN: I am not!
MATER: Are so!

00:08.633 --> 00:10.218
-McQUEEN: Am not!
-Are so!

00:10.301 --> 00:12.679
Cut it out, Mater. I'm not lost.

00:12.762 --> 00:15.515
If this is navigating,
then I'm a Tesla pickup.

00:15.640 --> 00:18.435
Yeah? Well, that crummy diner
you picked out gave me gas

00:18.518 --> 00:19.644
and not the good kind.

00:19.728 --> 00:22.313
Yeah, well, you make chewy,
smacky sounds in your sleep.

00:22.397 --> 00:23.398
And your breath!

00:23.481 --> 00:25.525
Well, your breath
smells like a carpet fire.

00:25.608 --> 00:27.569
Well, we'll just have
to agree to disagree.

00:27.652 --> 00:28.653
I can't agree to that.

00:28.737 --> 00:29.738
-Fine then!
-No, fine.

00:29.821 --> 00:30.822
-Fine.
-Fine!

00:30.905 --> 00:32.699
-Fine, fine, fine.
-Fine, fine, fine.

00:32.949 --> 00:34.117
Fine.

00:34.200 --> 00:35.952
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

00:38.204 --> 00:40.832
If we were speaking to each other,
which we're not,

00:40.915 --> 00:42.834
I'd say there's a camp up ahead.

00:42.917 --> 00:45.420
And if I was answering,
I'd say, "Woo-hoo!"

00:45.503 --> 00:46.629
(LAUGHS)

00:48.423 --> 00:50.759
Oh, I spy with my little eye

00:50.842 --> 00:54.304
two clackety-kitty cars have
lost their mumsies.

00:54.387 --> 00:56.723
Huh. Must be some
kind of regional dialect.

00:56.806 --> 00:57.807
I got this.

00:57.891 --> 00:59.642
We'll be rumblin' back to the rightwise

00:59.726 --> 01:02.687
if you cut us all slacksy-like,
Cap'n Long Leggy.

01:04.481 --> 01:05.482
(ALL SCREAM)

01:06.900 --> 01:10.779
<i>Hitting the highway, a couple of friends</i>

01:10.862 --> 01:14.741
<i>With new adventures 'round every bend</i>

01:14.824 --> 01:18.787
<i>Whether racing fast or getting towed</i>

01:18.870 --> 01:23.041
<i>We're ever together, cars on the road</i>

01:26.377 --> 01:29.130
"Here, I got this."
Yeah, you got this, all right.

01:29.214 --> 01:30.882
Well, I did, sorta.

01:30.965 --> 01:32.467
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

01:34.177 --> 01:35.220
Oh, yeah.

01:35.303 --> 01:36.429
(LAUGHTER)

01:36.513 --> 01:37.764
Let's go!

01:40.975 --> 01:42.977
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

01:48.525 --> 01:50.944
CARS: (CHANTING) Ho! Ha!

01:52.070 --> 01:54.447
Ho! Ha!

01:55.490 --> 01:57.784
Ho! Ha!

01:58.785 --> 02:01.287
Ho! Ha!

02:02.497 --> 02:04.791
Whoa. Points for pageantry.

02:06.167 --> 02:09.170
-Refugees from the decaying wastelands.
-(WHIMPERS)

02:10.255 --> 02:11.339
Wastelands?

02:11.422 --> 02:13.091
(CHUCKLES) We're from Radiator Springs.

02:13.174 --> 02:15.176
Maybe she means it metaphorically.

02:19.430 --> 02:22.725
You come crawling
for acceptance into our ranks?

02:22.809 --> 02:24.561
Um, no.

02:24.644 --> 02:26.896
Shall we drag you to the badlands

02:26.980 --> 02:30.108
where your parched husks
will be dismantled by scavengers?

02:30.275 --> 02:31.276
-Ow!
-(LAUGHS)

02:31.359 --> 02:34.904
Or will you prove your worth
in the Thundercone?

02:35.238 --> 02:36.739
-Well?
-Ow!

02:36.823 --> 02:38.825
Uh, cone. Yeah, cone sounds good.

02:38.908 --> 02:40.743
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

02:42.245 --> 02:45.498
Prepare them. The Thundercone awaits.

02:45.582 --> 02:49.752
CARS: (CHANTING) Thundercone!
Thundercone! Thundercone!

02:57.594 --> 02:59.220
(GASPS) Dadgum.

02:59.971 --> 03:01.764
How come you got a flamethrower?

03:01.890 --> 03:04.517
Well, you got a... shovelbeard.

03:04.601 --> 03:08.521
Two cars enter. One survives.

03:08.605 --> 03:09.606
(CARS LAUGHING)

03:12.108 --> 03:16.362
Let the victor join our ranks
to battle the army of opposition.

03:16.446 --> 03:17.697
CAR: Yeah!

03:18.198 --> 03:19.574
-The what?
-Who?

03:19.657 --> 03:20.700
Off you go!

03:20.783 --> 03:21.784
(BOTH SCREAM)

03:26.748 --> 03:29.292
-Now what do we do?
-I'll destroy you.

03:29.375 --> 03:31.085
Then try to wake you up later.

03:31.169 --> 03:32.670
What? No.

03:32.754 --> 03:34.339
I saw it on the TV.

03:34.422 --> 03:36.382
How about I destroy you?

03:36.466 --> 03:38.968
-Then--
-Nah. Nobody will believe that.

03:39.052 --> 03:40.428
-(GRUNTS)
-(LAUGHS)

03:40.511 --> 03:42.347
-See?
-Fine. Do your worst.

03:42.430 --> 03:44.265
-Fine. I will.
-Fine!

03:44.474 --> 03:46.309
-Fine, fine, fine!
-Fine, fine, fine!

03:47.310 --> 03:50.396
-Oh, wait. Where'd everybody go?
-Huh?

03:58.363 --> 04:00.698
The dust rises, the hordes approach.

04:00.782 --> 04:03.785
Many vital fluids
will be spilled this day.

04:03.868 --> 04:05.411
(CARS CHEERING)

04:05.495 --> 04:07.330
Now's our chance. You coming?

04:07.455 --> 04:11.960
Uh-uh. Take the line, lambsies.
There'll be no objectors in these ranks.

04:17.966 --> 04:19.926
They say you came from the wastelands.

04:20.009 --> 04:22.220
(SIGHS) What started all this anyway?

04:22.303 --> 04:24.597
A lifetime ago we came,

04:24.681 --> 04:27.976
<i>a gathering of like-minded,</i>
<i>artsy-craftsy campers,</i>

04:28.059 --> 04:30.186
seeking enlightenment in the desert.

04:30.270 --> 04:32.105
-And?
-I don't know.

04:32.188 --> 04:35.066
Petty squabbles flared. Factions formed.

04:35.149 --> 04:37.277
Old school clashed with the new.

04:37.777 --> 04:39.195
It's all a bit murky now.

04:39.279 --> 04:42.156
You don't even remember
what you're fighting about?

04:42.240 --> 04:44.284
(CHUCKLING) Not really, no.

04:44.534 --> 04:46.494
Maybe a little intervention is in order.

04:49.330 --> 04:50.915
Mater, follow me.

04:58.131 --> 04:59.966
(HORN TOOTING)

05:00.049 --> 05:01.718
(CARS YELLING)

05:15.023 --> 05:16.691
(HORN BLARING)

05:19.569 --> 05:22.196
Warring factions!

05:22.739 --> 05:24.115
Hey, we get it.

05:24.407 --> 05:27.076
A fun little trip among friends
somehow escalates

05:27.160 --> 05:29.329
into a post-apocalyptic turf war.

05:29.746 --> 05:31.164
It happens, right?

05:32.498 --> 05:35.043
But it's okay to lay down
your flamethrowers

05:35.126 --> 05:36.794
and forget these petty squabbles.

05:37.337 --> 05:38.713
Who cares?

05:40.340 --> 05:43.718
Some dopey, insignificant tiff
spins out of control.

05:43.801 --> 05:46.429
And next thing you know,
you and your best friend in the world

05:46.512 --> 05:49.515
have come to blows
over absolutely nothing.

05:49.599 --> 05:50.892
(CHUCKLES) It's crazy.

05:51.267 --> 05:53.603
-Right, buddy?
-Right, buddy.

05:55.229 --> 05:56.481
So what do you say?

05:56.564 --> 05:59.567
Why don't we all just throttle back,
shut the heck up,

05:59.650 --> 06:01.569
and, I don't know, move on?

06:01.903 --> 06:04.989
Come on. Can't be any worse
than all this, right?

06:13.706 --> 06:15.083
(ALL YELLING)

06:16.459 --> 06:17.877
-Over there!
-What is?

06:17.960 --> 06:18.961
McQUEEN: The highway!

06:21.798 --> 06:24.175
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

06:30.681 --> 06:32.225
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

06:32.308 --> 06:34.769
-(GASPS)
-(SLURPING)

06:36.354 --> 06:37.897
Oh, well, we gave it a try.

06:37.980 --> 06:39.899
At least this little fellow was listening.

06:40.233 --> 06:44.112
Your decaying wasteland
is a beautiful vision of hope.

06:44.195 --> 06:45.571
Yes, it is.

06:46.614 --> 06:49.117
Uh, Lightning, take a look.

06:52.370 --> 06:53.788
(LAUGHS)

06:55.790 --> 06:59.419
Ah. I guess I'll go in and order
a couple hundred more sippy coolers.

07:00.586 --> 07:03.673
(SLURPING)
